net.ashwork.functionality.primitive.doubles

Interface ToDoubleFunction1<T1>

  • Type Parameters:
    T1 - the type of the input to the function
    All Superinterfaces:
    Arity, FunctionN<java.lang.Double>, InputChainable<T1>, InputChainableInput<T1>, ResultChainable<java.lang.Double>, ResultChainableResult<java.lang.Double>, ToDoubleFunctionN, UnboxedResult<Function1<T1,java.lang.Double>>, Variant<java.util.function.ToDoubleFunction<T1>>
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface ToDoubleFunction1<T1>
extends ToDoubleFunctionN, InputChainableInput<T1>, UnboxedResult<Function1<T1,java.lang.Double>>, Variant<java.util.function.ToDoubleFunction<T1>>
    Represents a function that accepts one argument and produces a double-valued result. This is the one-arity specialization of ToDoubleFunctionN. This is the double-producing primitive specialization of Function1.

    This is a functional interface whose functional method is applyAsDouble(Object).

    Since:
    3.0.0
